{{Infobox book | name = Counting the Eons | title_orig = | translator = | image = File:CountingTheEons.jpg | border = yes | caption = First edition | author = [[Isaac Asimov]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = Kyoshi Kanai<ref>http://www.abebooks.co.uk/servlet/BookDetailsPL?bi=417701852</ref> | country = United States | language = English | series = [[Fantasy & Science Fiction]] essays | subject = | genre = | publisher = [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]] | pub_date = 7 January 1983 | english_pub_date = | media_type = print ([[Hardback]] and [[Paperback]]) | pages = | isbn = | oclc = | preceded_by = [[The Sun Shines Bright (book)|The Sun Shines Bright]] | followed_by = [[X Stands for Unknown|'X' Stands for Unknown]] }}
'''''Counting the Eons''''' is a collection of seventeen nonfiction science essays written by [[Isaac Asimov]]. It was the sixteenth of a series of books collecting essays from ''[[The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction]]'', these being first published between August 1980 and December 1981. It was first published by [[Doubleday & Company]] in 1983.
